# Public "jiva" repo — WHITELIST policy.
# This repo is PUBLIC. It must only ever contain the marketing website and the
# Jiva.dmg (attached as a GitHub Release asset, not committed here).
# NOTHING private/source belongs here. See REPO-POLICY.md.
#
# Strategy: ignore everything, then re-allow only the approved files.

# 1) ignore everything by default
*

# 2) re-allow the approved public files
!.gitignore
!index.html
!README.md
!REPO-POLICY.md
# CNAME binds the jiva.works custom domain to GitHub Pages — must be re-allowed
# here or `git add -A` silently ignores it and the domain 404s (fixed 2026-07-20).
!CNAME
